welcome.name: Welcome
welcome.content:
![Sapphire Logo](https://cdn.skyra.pw/gh-assets/sapphire-banner.png) # Sapphire **A pleasant Discord Bot framework** [![GitHub](https://img.shields.io/github/license/sapphiredev/framework)](https://github.com/sapphiredev/framework/blob/main/LICENSE.md) [![codecov](https://codecov.io/gh/sapphiredev/framework/branch/main/graph/badge.svg?token=AHPITY8WY9)](https://codecov.io/gh/sapphiredev/framework) [![npm](https://img.shields.io/npm/v/@sapphire/framework?color=crimson&logo=npm&style=flat-square)](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@sapphire/framework) [![Support Server](https://discord.com/api/guilds/737141877803057244/embed.png?style=banner2)](https://sapphirejs.dev/discord)
--- ## Description Sapphire is a Discord bot framework built on top of [discord.js] for advanced and amazing bots.
| [**Click here for the documentation and guides**](https://www.sapphirejs.dev/) | | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
## Features - Written in TypeScript - Command Handler, Arguments, Pre-conditions and Listeners Store - Completely Modular and Extendable - Advanced Plugins Support - Supports many [plugins](https://github.com/sapphiredev/plugins) - Full TypeScript & JavaScript support ## Installation `@sapphire/framework` depends on the following packages. Be sure to install these along with this package! - [`discord.js`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/discord.js) You can use the following command to install this package, or replace `npm install` with your package manager of choice. ```sh npm install @sapphire/framework discord.js ``` --- ## Buy us some doughnuts Sapphire Community is and always will be open source, even if we don't get donations. That being said, we know there are amazing people who may still want to donate just to show their appreciation. Thank you very much in advance! We accept donations through Open Collective, Ko-fi, Paypal, Patreon and GitHub Sponsorships. You can use the buttons below to donate through your method of choice. | Donate With | Address | | :-------------: | :-------------------------------------------------: | | Open Collective | [Click Here](https://sapphirejs.dev/opencollective) | | Ko-fi | [Click Here](https://sapphirejs.dev/kofi) | | Patreon | [Click Here](https://sapphirejs.dev/patreon) | | PayPal | [Click Here](https://sapphirejs.dev/paypal) | ## Contributors ‚ú® Thanks goes to these wonderful people ([emoji key](https://allcontributors.org/docs/en/emoji-key)):

classes.name: PreconditionContainerArray
classes.description: An {@link IPreconditionContainer} that defines an array of multiple {@link IPreconditionContainer}s.
classes.extendedDescription:
By default, array containers run either of two conditions: AND and OR ({@link PreconditionRunCondition}), the top level
will always default to AND, where the nested one flips the logic (OR, then children arrays are AND, then OR...).

This allows `['Connect', ['Moderator', ['DJ', 'SongAuthor']]]` to become a thrice-nested precondition container, where:
- Level 1: [Single(Connect), Array] runs AND, both containers must return a successful value.
- Level 2: [Single(Moderator), Array] runs OR, either container must return a successful value.
- Level 3: [Single(DJ), Single(SongAuthor)] runs AND, both containers must return a successful value.

In other words, it is identical to doing:
```typescript
Connect && (Moderator || (DJ && SongAuthor));
```

* An array of strings, e.g. [`silent`].
* A boolean defining whether the strategy should accept all keys (`true`) or none at all (`false`).

props.description: Sets whether or not the command should be treated as NSFW. If set to true, the `NSFW` precondition will be added to the list.

props.name: options
props.description:
The accepted options. Options are key-value identifiers that can be placed anywhere in the command. Two different types are accepted:
* An array of strings, e.g. [`silent`].
* A boolean defining whether the strategy should accept all keys (`true`) or none at all (`false`).

props.name: preconditions
props.description: The {@link Precondition}s to be run, accepts an array of their names.

props.name: prefixes
props.description: The prefixes for both flags and options.

props.name: quotes
props.description: The quotes accepted by this command, pass `[]` to disable them.
props.default:
[
  ['"', '"'], // Double quotes
  ['‚Äú', '‚Äù'], // Fancy quotes (on iOS)
  ['„Äå', '„Äç'] // Corner brackets (CJK)
]

props.name: requiredClientPermissions
props.description: The required permissions for the client.

props.name: requiredUserPermissions
props.description: The required permissions for the user.

props.name: runIn
props.description: The channels the command should run in. If set to `null`, no precondition entry will be added. Some optimizations are applied when given an array to reduce the amount of preconditions run (e.g. `'GUILD_TEXT'` and `'GUILD_NEWS'` becomes `'GUILD_ANY'`, and if both `'DM'` and `'GUILD_ANY'` are defined, then no precondition entry is added as it runs in all channels).

props.name: separators
props.description: The flag separators.

props.name: typing
props.description:
If {@link SapphireClient.typing} is true, this option will override it.
Otherwise, this option has no effect - you may call {@link Channel#sendTyping}` in the run method if you want specific commands to display the typing status.

props.name: commandId
props.description: The id of the command.

props.name: commandName
props.description: The name of the command.

props.name: parameter
props.description:
The canonical parameter specified by the user in the command, as
a string, equivalent to the first parameter of {@link Argument#run}.
This allows {@link ExtendedArgument#handle} to access the original
argument, which is useful for returning {@link Argument#error} so
that you don't have to convert the parsed argument back into a
string.

props.name: baseArgument
props.description:
The name of the underlying argument whose value is used to compute
the extended argument value; see {@link ArgType} for valid keys.

props.name: name
props.description: The name of the argument, this is used to make the identification of an argument easier.

props.name: run
props.description: The method which is called when invoking the argument.

props.name: debug
props.description: Alias of {@link ILogger.write} with {@link LogLevel.Debug} as level.

props.name: error
props.description: Alias of {@link ILogger.write} with {@link LogLevel.Error} as level.

props.name: fatal
props.description: Alias of {@link ILogger.write} with {@link LogLevel.Fatal} as level.

props.name: has
props.description: Checks whether a level is supported.

props.name: info
props.description: Alias of {@link ILogger.write} with {@link LogLevel.Info} as level.

props.name: trace
props.description: Alias of {@link ILogger.write} with {@link LogLevel.Trace} as level.

props.name: warn
props.description: Alias of {@link ILogger.write} with {@link LogLevel.Warn} as level.

props.name: write
props.description: Writes the log message given a level and the value(s).

typedefs.name: IPreconditionCondition
typedefs.description: Defines the condition for {@link PreconditionContainerArray}s to run.

props.name: chatInputParallel
props.description: Runs all the containers using `Promise.all`, then checks the results once all tasks finished running.

props.name: chatInputSequential
props.description: Runs the containers one by one.

props.name: contextMenuParallel
props.description: Runs all the containers using `Promise.all`, then checks the results once all tasks finished running.

props.name: contextMenuSequential
props.description: Runs the containers one by one.

props.name: messageParallel
props.description: Runs all the containers using `Promise.all`, then checks the results once all tasks finished running.

props.name: messageSequential
props.description: Runs the containers one by one.

typedefs.name: IPreconditionContainer
typedefs.description: An abstracted precondition container to be implemented by classes.

props.name: chatInputRun
props.description: Runs a precondition container.

props.name: contextMenuRun
props.description: Runs a precondition container.

props.name: messageRun
props.description: Runs a precondition container.

props.name: interactionHandlerType
props.description: The type of interaction this handler is for. Must be one of {@link InteractionHandlerTypes}.

props.name: commandName
props.description: The alias used to run this command.

props.name: commandPrefix
props.description:
The matched prefix, this will always be the same as {@link MessageCommand.RunContext.prefix} if it was a string, otherwise it is
the result of doing `prefix.exec(content)[0]`.

props.name: prefix
props.description: The prefix used to run this command.

typedefs.name: PreconditionArrayResolvableDetails
typedefs.description:
Defines the detailed options for the {@link PreconditionContainerArray}, where both the {@link PreconditionRunMode} and the
entries can be defined.

props.name: entries
props.description: The data that will be used to resolve {@link IPreconditionContainer} dependent of this one.

props.name: mode
props.description: The mode the {@link PreconditionContainerArray} will run.

props.name: position
props.description:
The position for the precondition to be set at in the global precondition list. If set to `null`, this
precondition will not be set as a global one.

typedefs.name: PreconditionSingleResolvableDetails
typedefs.description:
Defines the detailed options for the {@link PreconditionContainerSingle}, where both the {@link PreconditionContext} and the
name of the precondition can be defined.

props.name: context
props.description: The context to be set at {@link PreconditionContainerSingle.context}.

props.name: name
props.description: The name of the precondition to retrieve from {@link SapphireClient.preconditions}.

typedefs.name: Preconditions
typedefs.description:
The registered preconditions and their contexts, if any. When registering new ones, it is recommended to use
[module augmentation](https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/declaration-merging.html#module-augmentation) so
custom ones are registered.
typedefs.extendedDescription:
When a key's value is `never`, it means that it does not take any context, which allows you to pass its identifier as
a bare string (e.g. `preconditions: ['NSFW']`), however, if context is required, a non-`never` type should be passed,
which will type {@link PreconditionContainerArray#append} and require an object with the name and a `context` with
the defined type.

props.name: times
props.description: The maximum amount of times the argument can be repeated.

props.name: baseUserDirectory
props.description:
The base user directory, if set to `null`, Sapphire will not call {@link StoreRegistry.registerPath},
meaning that you will need to manually set each folder for each store. Please read the aforementioned method's
documentation for more information.

props.name: caseInsensitiveCommands
props.description: Whether commands can be case insensitive

props.name: caseInsensitivePrefixes
props.description: Whether prefixes can be case insensitive

props.name: defaultCooldown
props.description: Sets the default cooldown time for all commands.

props.name: defaultPrefix
props.description: The default prefix, in case of `null`, only mention prefix will trigger the bot's commands.

props.name: disableMentionPrefix
props.description: Controls whether the bot has mention as a prefix disabled

props.name: enableLoaderTraceLoggings
props.description: Whether or not trace logging should be enabled.

props.name: fetchPrefix
props.description: The prefix hook, by default it is a callback function that returns {@link SapphireClientOptions.defaultPrefix}.

props.name: id
props.description: The client's ID, this is automatically set by the CoreReady event.

props.name: loadDefaultErrorListeners
props.description: If Sapphire should load the pre-included error event listeners that log any encountered errors to the {@link SapphireClient.logger} instance

props.name: loadMessageCommandListeners
props.description: If Sapphire should load the pre-included message command listeners that are used to process incoming messages for commands.

props.name: logger
props.description: The logger options, defaults to an instance of {@link Logger} when {@link ClientLoggerOptions.instance} is not specified.

props.name: preventFailedToFetchLogForGuildIds
props.description:
Whenever starting the bot process Sapphire may report errors when failing to fetch guild commands.
One of the causes for this can be when a bot was invited to a server without the `application.commands` scope.

props.name: regexPrefix
props.description: The regex prefix, an alternative to a mention or regular prefix to allow creating natural language command messages

props.name: typing
props.description: Controls whether the bot will automatically appear to be typing when a command is accepted.

typedefs.name: SimplePreconditionSingleResolvableDetails
typedefs.description:
Defines the simple options for the {@link PreconditionContainerSingle}, where only the name of the precondition can
be defined.

props.name: name
props.description: The name of the precondition to retrieve from {@link SapphireClient.preconditions}.

typedefs.name: ArgumentResult
typedefs.description: Defines a synchronous result of an {@link Argument}, check {@link Argument.AsyncResult} for the asynchronous version.

typedefs.name: AsyncArgumentResult
typedefs.description: Defines an asynchronous result of an {@link Argument}, check {@link Argument.Result} for the synchronous version.

typedefs.name: AsyncPreconditionContainerReturn
typedefs.description: Async-only version of {@link PreconditionContainerReturn}, to be used when the run method is async.

typedefs.name: CommandOptionsRunType
typedefs.description: The allowed values for {@link Command.Options.runIn}.

typedefs.name: PreconditionArrayResolvable
typedefs.description: Defines the data accepted by {@link PreconditionContainerArray}'s constructor.

typedefs.name: PreconditionContainerResult
typedefs.description: Defines the result's value for a PreconditionContainer.

typedefs.name: PreconditionContainerReturn
typedefs.description: Defines the return type of the generic {@link IPreconditionContainer.messageRun}.

typedefs.name: PreconditionEntryResolvable
typedefs.description: Defines the data accepted for each entry of the array.

typedefs.name: PreconditionSingleResolvable
typedefs.description: Defines the data accepted by {@link PreconditionContainerSingle}'s constructor.

typedefs.name: SapphirePrefix
typedefs.description:
A valid prefix in Sapphire.
* `string`: a single prefix, e.g. `'!'`.
* `string[]`: an array of prefixes, e.g. `['!', '.']`.
* `null`: disabled prefix, locks the bot's command usage to mentions only.

props.name: behaviorWhenNotIdentical
props.description: Specifies what we should do when the command is present, but not identical with the data you provided

props.name: guildIds
props.description: If this is specified, the application commands will only be registered for these guild ids.

props.name: idHints
props.description: Specifies a list of command ids that we should check in the event of a name mismatch

props.name: registerCommandIfMissing
props.description: If we should register the command when it is missing

props.name: argument
props.description: The argument that caused the error.

props.name: context
props.description: The extra context to provide more information about this error.

props.name: identifier
props.description: The identifier.

props.name: message
props.description: The message to be passed to the Error constructor.

props.name: parameter
props.description: The parameter that failed to be parsed.

props.name: context
props.description: The extra context to provide more information about this error.

props.name: identifier
props.description: The identifier.

props.name: message
props.description: The message to be passed to the Error constructor.

props.name: precondition
props.description: The precondition that caused the error.

props.name: context
props.description: The extra context to provide more information about this error.

props.name: identifier
props.description: The identifier for this error.

props.name: message
props.description: The message to be passed to the Error constructor.
